/p>\n<h4 style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Notes:<\/strong><\/h4>\n<ol>\n<li>If you\u2019ve already generated a set of API credentials, you\u2019ll have to delete your existing set before you can generate a new set of credentials. In this case, you\u2019ll see a View API Signature (or Certificate) link where the Request API credentials link is circled in the diagram above. Click the View API Signature&gt; link, and on the page that appears, click the Remove button to delete the existing signature.<\/li>\n<li>You need Business Merchant account to setup PayPal API working.<\/li>\n<li>Always test before setting online payment method to production.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<h3><strong>Troubleshooting<\/strong><\/h3>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/security-header-not-valid-when-setting-up-paypal\/\">Security Header Not Valid when Setting up Paypal<\/a><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>To setup Paypal you will need API permissions. PayPal API Username PayPal API Password API Signature Follow the steps below to get the API permissions Creating an API signature Log in to your PayPal business account at www.paypal.com. Click the profile icon (Profile menu) on the top right side of the page. From the Business [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"footnotes":""},"categories":[4],"tags":[],"class_list":["post-832","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","hentry","category-payment-gateways"],"aioseo_notices":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/832","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[